The paper discusses the application of Continuous Delivery in safety-critical domains, which suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and safety and security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the need for formal verification and safety analysis, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The guidelines proposed in the paper may involve programming languages and tools (cs.PL) and machine learning (cs.LG) to automate safety analysis.
